{
  "texts": [
    "The crucial idea behind the algorithm is that the Legendre transform can actually be understood in a stronger sense.",
    "This relies on describing the formal data of the connections à la Deligne-Malgrange, in terms of the exponential local system I.",
    "In brief, I is an infinite collection of circles covering the circle ∂ of directions around infinity.",
    "These circles represent all the possible exponents of a connection at ∞ (see §2.1 for a review of the exponential local system).",
    "The stronger version of the Legendre transform is then the following Crucial idea: The Legendre transform provides a self-homeomorphism ℓ of the collection I >1 of all circles in I of slope > 1 at infinity (see [Mal91, Dou23] and §5.1)."
  ]
}